        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A small number of pre-production power steering pump drive gears were released to the power
                    steering pump supplier that could result in the wrong gear being installed on the Maxxforce 7
                    engines. The center distance between the driving and driven gears may not be adequate for the gears
                    to mesh without interference. This leads to stress, fatigue and spalling of the PS Pump gear teeth.
                    It can eventually lead to low oil pressure symptoms resulting from metal in the oil pan, and
                    eventually engine failure.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
